Package: geostools
Title: An R package of tools to assist with handling geoscientific problems
Version: 0.1.0
Author:
  Thomas Muench [aut, cre],
  Andrew Dolman [aut],
  Thomas Laepple [aut]
Maintainer: Thomas Muench <thomas.muench@awi.de>
Description: This package contains various functions to assist with the handling
  of geoscientific problems; such as calculating distances between two points on
  Earth, interpolating between points of a latitude-longitude grid, doing
  coordinate conversions, etc.
Depends: R (>= 3.5)
License: file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
Imports:
    geosphere (>= 1.5.10),
    geometry (>= 0.4.5)
Suggests:
    pfields (>= 0.2.1.9000)
Remotes:
    earthsystemdiagnostics/pfields
URL: https://github.com/EarthSystemDiagnostics/geotools	
BugReports: https://github.com/EarthSystemDiagnostics/geotools/issues
